<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-28T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-28T03:00:00-05:00" n="574" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.91262/327: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-28T10:00:00+02:00">June 28,
                                    1941—10 a.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 12:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2595. My 1974, May 20, noon. The Foreign Office has orally informed the
                            Embassy that the Reich Minister of Justice has agreed to permit
                            fortnightly visits to Hottelet by an officer of the Embassy. The formal
                            notification of this decision has not yet been received and several days
                            may elapse before the first visit can be arranged.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>